@node "_requirements"  "  REQUIREMENTS  "
@next "_installation"
@prev "Main"

AFM 3.0 won't work without:


[1] YAM (should be at least 2.0, I haven't tested it with earlier versions)

[2] YAM: assign to the Yam directory

[3] MUI 3.8, might work with earlier versions.

[4] Rexx mounted

  Should run on any machine that uses MUI 3.8. and Yam2.0
  It was coded on an A1230T with 32Mb fast, a 2.5Gb Hd, Blitz 2,
  using Yam 2 preview 6.

@endnode

@node "_installation"  "  INSTALLATION  "
@prev "_requirements"

Energy equals the mass multiplying by the square of ligth speed...
Easy ain't it :)


Just double click on the install icon...

The following files are copied:

    AFM3 dir   -> Wherever you choose
    AFM3.guide -> Help:

The prefs for AFM3 are stored in ENVARC: under the name AFM.options

@endnode

@node "_usage"  "  USING AFM3.0  "
@prev "_installation"

Main Page

    Actions Group:

    o Request Recent Uploads
      This button is used to send a mail to Aminet requesting
      the last 7 days uploaded files. The reply is pretty fast...
      Just wait for 10/20 seconds for it...

    o Join Splitted Mails
      When files are bigger than 512Kb they are broken into several
      mails. This button joins the mails into a single one so that
      the attachment can be saved.

    o Save Options
      Erh.... Save the options?

    o Contact Author
      This button opens a new mail addressed to me...

    o About
      Pops a requester with some info.


    Options Group:

    o Reply to
      This string is used for you to define the Email address that you
      want the files sent to. Don't give any address if you want to
      use your normal Email [default].

    o FTP Server Email
      This string is where you type the email address of the FTP
      Server you want to to use. ftp-mail@uni-paderborn.de is the
      default. (Please note this server only sends mail at 17.00)

    o FTP Server to Open
      Some FTP Email Servers don't have the files on them so they go
      get them on another server. If this is the case you must set
      the ftp server that they must access to retrieve the Mail.
      By default that is not needed has ftp-mail@uni-paderborn.de has
      all the files on it.

    o Yam Aminet Folder
      This is where you select the folder (in Yam) where the Aminet
      mail is stored. The default is Incoming.
      E.G. I move all my Aminet mail to a Folder called Aminet.

    o Download .Readme Files
      If this is set the Readme files will be sent with the file.
      No is the default.


DownLoad Page

    o Make Request
      After you have selected some files from the list, this button
      will write a mail requesting those files to be sent to to you :)

    o Check Folder
      This button will make AFM search for any mails from Aminet
      containing Upload info. A progress bar is displayed showing
      what's going on...

@endnode

